### ========================================
### API TESTING GUIDE (VS Code REST Client)
### ========================================
# Install the "REST Client" extension in VS Code.
# You can click "Send Request" above any of the requests below to test directly.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
# Replace these with real IDs when testing manually
@incidentId = YOUR_INCIDENT_ID
@notificationId = YOUR_NOTIFICATION_ID

### ----------------------------------------
### 1. AUTHENTICATION
### ----------------------------------------

### Login as User (Replace credentials as needed)
# @name loginUser
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@test.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Login as Staff (Replace credentials as needed)
# @name loginStaff
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "staff@test.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Logout Current User (Requires Login)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout



### ----------------------------------------
### 2. USER ACTIONS (Requires User Login)
### ----------------------------------------

### Report a New Incident (AI will classify it!)
POST {{baseUrl}}/incidents/report
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Smoke coming out of Room 304",
  "description": "Thick black smoke is billowing from under the door of room 304.",
  "location": "3rd Floor / Room 304"
}

### Get My Incidents
GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents/my-incidents

### Get Specific Incident By ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents/{{incidentId}}


### ----------------------------------------
### 3. STAFF ACTIONS (Requires Staff Login)
### ----------------------------------------

### Get Dashboard Counts
GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents/dashboard

### Get All Incidents (You can add ?status=Pending&severity=Critical)
GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents/all

### Update Incident Status
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/incidents/{{incidentId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Active"
}

### Update Incident to Resolved
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/incidents/{{incidentId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Resolved"
}


### ----------------------------------------
### 4. NOTIFICATIONS (Staff or User)
### ----------------------------------------

### Get All Notifications
GET {{baseUrl}}/notifications/

### Mark ALL Notifications as Read
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/notifications/read-all

### Mark Single Notification as Read
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/notifications/{{notificationId}}/read
